381
00:17:51,279 --> 00:17:52,200
No, it's not.

382
00:17:52,799 --> 00:17:54,000
Isn't it fine now?

383
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,839
He talks less, I listen less.

384
00:17:56,119 --> 00:17:57,200
The whole world goes quiet.

385
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:01,720
These past two years, your mom

386
00:18:02,359 --> 00:18:03,480
has helped your big brother with his kids.

387
00:18:04,079 --> 00:18:05,480
It's just you and your dad at home.

388
00:18:06,319 --> 00:18:07,359
All your dad's attention

389
00:18:07,359 --> 00:18:08,559
is focused on you now.

390
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:10,279
All the pressure falls on you.

391
00:18:10,559 --> 00:18:11,200
On his side,

392
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:13,119
I'll go talk to him.

393
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:14,839
And you,

394
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,680
try to understand him too.

395
00:18:17,319 --> 00:18:18,319
I know.

396
00:18:19,119 --> 00:18:20,960
My dad's scolded me more than once or twice.

397
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:21,480
Right?

398
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:23,319
Are you underestimating me?

399
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,200
I may not be that capable,

400
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:26,359
but I'm pretty thick-skinned.

401
00:18:26,759 --> 00:18:27,319
Besides,

402
00:18:27,839 --> 00:18:28,960
if he tells me to cook, I cook.

403
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:30,559
He tells me to practice knife skills, I do.

404
00:18:30,559 --> 00:18:31,240
He says listen to An Dong,

405
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,359
so I listen, that's all.

406
00:18:32,599 --> 00:18:33,799
What else can he say?

407
00:18:35,319 --> 00:18:37,119
You're way too passive.

408
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:37,839
Bro,

409
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:39,079
stop worrying, okay?

410
00:18:39,079 --> 00:18:40,880
If you keep worrying, you'll go gray.

411
00:18:41,559 --> 00:18:42,680
I'm not a little kid.

412
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:43,759
I'm not clueless.

413
00:18:44,279 --> 00:18:45,319
Honestly, what you mean

414
00:18:45,319 --> 00:18:46,839
I understand perfectly.

415
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:48,480
Don't worry.

416
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:51,440
Alright.

417
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,279
This restaurant renovation—

418
00:18:57,079 --> 00:18:58,119
Did An Dong pay for it?

419
00:18:59,119 --> 00:18:59,799
About how much?

420
00:19:00,839 --> 00:19:01,599
I don't know.

421
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:03,960
Go ahead and get busy.

422
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:04,799
Okay, I'm heading over.

423
00:19:05,599 --> 00:19:06,079
Don't worry.

424
00:19:11,799 --> 00:19:15,119
Do you think my brother likes Nana?

425
00:19:15,559 --> 00:19:17,720
He eagerly went to make Xuehualiang for her.

426
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:19,359
I thought they'd get together.

427
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:20,480
But after he came back,

428
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,000
they're still just like before.

429
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:24,720
I asked him to help with my promo stuff.

430
00:19:24,759 --> 00:19:25,519
He said he was busy.

431
00:19:25,519 --> 00:19:26,759
Turned me down flat.

432
00:19:26,759 --> 00:19:27,920
Really firm about it.

433
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:28,799
Don't worry.

434
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,559
Mingliang knows better than both of us.

435
00:19:30,759 --> 00:19:32,079
You don't really know him.

436
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:33,880
He cares more about me and Ankar

437
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,440
than he does about himself.

438
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:36,440
You know that.

439
00:19:36,519 --> 00:19:37,160
My dad—

440
00:19:37,519 --> 00:19:38,400
To put it nicely,

441
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,440
he's a workaholic.

442
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,759
As my mom says,

443
00:19:41,759 --> 00:19:43,200
he's a muddle-headed guy.

444
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:45,400
He's always muddle-headed in life.

445
00:19:45,759 --> 00:19:46,720
Since I was little,

446
00:19:46,759 --> 00:19:48,519
Mingliang looked after me more than he did.

447
00:19:48,799 --> 00:19:50,119
Take this time for example—

448
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,519
I wanted

449
00:19:51,759 --> 00:19:53,880
him to share some of my stress.

450
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,559
But then I thought,

451
00:19:55,759 --> 00:19:58,079
he's lived the same routine for years—

452
00:19:58,079 --> 00:19:59,359
just the restaurant,

453
00:19:59,480 --> 00:19:59,960
home,

454
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:00,799
and work.

455
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,200
Nowhere else.

456
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:03,440
When he rides alone,

457
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:05,440
I'm worried he'll get into trouble.

458
00:20:05,559 --> 00:20:07,000
If he goes again,

459
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,799
he'll just make things worse for my mom.

460
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,759
Then I'll be in even more trouble.

461
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,119
Yueyue,

462
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,160
I've met Uncle.

463
00:20:27,079 --> 00:20:28,680
Hello, Uncle.

464
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:50,839
Alright, stop working.

465
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,440
Have a seat.

466
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:09,960
Uncle Hu

467
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:12,960
Actually, before I met Yueyue

468
00:21:13,559 --> 00:21:14,480
I had already heard about you

469
00:21:15,039 --> 00:21:16,079
It was from a

470
00:21:16,079 --> 00:21:18,200
welder who helped build the factory

471
00:21:18,759 --> 00:21:19,400
He said

472
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:21,160
you were the best welder he'd ever met

473
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:24,240
He said you could weld eggshells
with your eyes closed

474
00:21:24,319 --> 00:21:25,359
without breaking the membrane

475
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,640
And you’re still just as skilled

476
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:28,279
Yes, yes

477
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:29,279
Your skills are amazing

478
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:30,920
I just never expected

479
00:21:31,039 --> 00:21:32,839
you were actually Yueyue’s father

480
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:34,680
I also heard

481
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,680
besides your own factory work

482
00:21:37,039 --> 00:21:38,519
you often help other companies

483
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:39,400
and train apprentices

484
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,960
You balance work and family perfectly

485
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:42,880
Alright, that's enough

486
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:44,920
Don’t think a few nice words

487
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:45,799
will make me help you

488
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:47,920
Young man

489
00:21:48,359 --> 00:21:50,200
When I was courting my wife

490
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,000
I welded for her

491
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,680
two tightly connected gears

492
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,000
I told her

493
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,480
the big one is me

494
00:21:58,839 --> 00:21:59,759
the small one is her

495
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:01,559
I would lead her

496
00:22:01,799 --> 00:22:03,359
and make our life wonderful

497
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:10,920
But after a lifetime fixing machines

498
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,720
I still couldn’t fix my own family

499
00:22:14,559 --> 00:22:15,839
Uncle, don’t say that

500
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:17,759
You’ve taken great care of your family

501
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:23,000
Back then, I was just like you

502
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,880
I came to Xinjiang alone

503
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,720
My parents weren’t with me

504
00:22:30,119 --> 00:22:31,119
And the two kids

505
00:22:31,279 --> 00:22:32,400
Mama Bayar

506
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,279
raised them herself

507
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:36,880
When Yueyue was born

508
00:22:37,559 --> 00:22:38,680
I was out of town for repairs

509
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,039
I only found out when I got back

510
00:22:42,039 --> 00:22:43,119
Yueyue was born premature

511
00:22:44,759 --> 00:22:45,960
If it weren’t for Aysha

512
00:22:52,559 --> 00:22:53,319
Young man

513
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:56,200
Marriage and love are not the same

514
00:22:57,079 --> 00:22:58,400
You can’t rely on a moment’s passion

515
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,160
As Yueyue’s parents

516
00:23:01,799 --> 00:23:03,759
we don’t want our daughter

517
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:06,559
to marry someone who neglects family

518
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,680
But we also don’t want

519
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:12,759
her to marry someone she doesn’t love

520
00:23:13,119 --> 00:23:13,720
If that happens

521
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:15,480
she’ll never be happy

522
00:23:17,519 --> 00:23:18,039
Uncle

523
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:20,839
I promise Yueyue will never be unhappy

524
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,200
Look at that heliostat

525
00:23:33,039 --> 00:23:34,960
Only when it’s at the right angle

526
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:36,960
can it catch the sunlight

527
00:23:37,319 --> 00:23:38,200
and gather energy

528
00:23:38,559 --> 00:23:39,680
Between you and Yueyue

529
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:42,000
you must find the right way and approach

530
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:43,960
to find your happiness together

531
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:53,160
I didn’t expect my dad would go to the station
just for us

532
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:54,680
He made a special trip to the power station

533
00:23:55,519 --> 00:23:57,039
There’s more you didn’t expect

534
00:23:57,759 --> 00:23:58,519
What else?

535
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,559
Uncle came here

536
00:24:00,759 --> 00:24:02,240
because Mingliang arranged it

537
00:24:06,079 --> 00:24:07,480
Alright, stop crying

538
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:08,799
So many people love you

539
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:10,359
You should be happy, right?

540
00:24:10,799 --> 00:24:12,720
My silly brother

541
00:24:13,799 --> 00:24:15,720
when it comes to his own problems

542
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,359
he’s just like a muddle-headed fool

543
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,000
But for our issues

544
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,319
he always has a solution

545
00:24:31,759 --> 00:24:32,400
Bayar

546
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,119
You’re back

547
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:34,960
Old Hu

548
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:36,119
Our family’s muddle-head

549
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:37,599
is really something

550
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:39,279
Didn’t even say hello

551
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:41,279
Went off to the Gobi and came back

552
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:42,960
But we have Mingliang

553
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,400
He planned the route perfectly

554
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,640
Even if I wanted to get lost

555
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:47,559
I couldn’t

556
00:24:49,039 --> 00:24:50,160
Go wash your hands

557
00:24:51,119 --> 00:24:52,559
Who told you to cook so deliciously

558
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,480
The smell made me dizzy

559
00:24:54,519 --> 00:24:55,400
Cut it out

560
00:24:55,559 --> 00:24:57,000
You think a few words

561
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:58,200
can fool me?

562
00:24:58,640 --> 00:24:59,200
I’m telling you

563
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,880
I’ll settle things with Mingliang tomorrow

564
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,559
You traitors

565
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:03,960
all teamed up to trick me

566
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:06,480
It’s because you and Yueyue are so capable

567
00:25:06,559 --> 00:25:08,839
One sneaks around with her mom

568
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:11,440
One goes off alone, leaving the group

569
00:25:11,599 --> 00:25:12,359
I’ve seen it all

570
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:14,519
Only I, the dad

571
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,839
have to go meet this guy

572
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:18,920
Did you meet him?

573
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:19,440
How was it?

574
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,200
I didn’t meet him first

575
00:25:22,839 --> 00:25:23,519
I was at the factory

576
00:25:23,519 --> 00:25:24,319
walked around a bit

577
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,319
asked around about him

578
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:28,119
What did they say?

579
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:29,599
They said he’s a good guy

580
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:32,799
He’s an outstanding worker every year

581
00:25:33,119 --> 00:25:34,240
Just like I was back in the day

582
00:25:36,039 --> 00:25:37,400
I didn’t ask about his job

583
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:39,240
I asked what kind of person he is

584
00:25:39,599 --> 00:25:40,400
