let the experts handle professional work.

876
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:24,400
Times are changing,

877
00:38:24,679 --> 00:38:26,360
and so are my views.

878
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:28,000
That's the only reason.

879
00:38:30,079 --> 00:38:31,960
I'm just afraid you'll lose yourself.

880
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:36,480
Child,

881
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:40,880
your hands are meant for painting.

882
00:38:41,239 --> 00:38:42,920
Your brushes must never dry out.

883
00:38:43,159 --> 00:38:45,400
Your eyes should see a bigger world.

884
00:38:45,639 --> 00:38:47,039
Don't just stare at the ledger.

885
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,320
Your heart

886
00:38:48,559 --> 00:38:50,920
should feel life's vibrant colors.

887
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:52,920
Even if you face setbacks,

888
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:53,800
or get hurt,

889
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:55,880
don't let the restaurant be your whole world.

890
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:02,000
Did Yueyue

891
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:03,679
tell you about the promo video?

892
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:05,119
It's not just that.

893
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:09,119
I want you to have more personal space.

894
00:39:09,239 --> 00:39:10,239
That's why I did this.

895
00:39:11,639 --> 00:39:13,119
I want to try, too.

896
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:15,880
If An Dong ever leaves one day,

897
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:18,960
we can always hire another professional manager.

898
00:39:19,519 --> 00:39:22,360
They're better at running restaurants than us.

899
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:33,760
Ankar actually listens to An Dong.

900
00:39:36,119 --> 00:39:38,039
An Dong sees his strengths.

901
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:41,159
We see them too.

902
00:39:43,119 --> 00:39:44,000
It's different.

903
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:46,760
For Ankar,

904
00:39:47,119 --> 00:39:48,280
An Dong is more neutral,

905
00:39:48,519 --> 00:39:49,360
more objective.

906
00:39:50,679 --> 00:39:51,440
Maybe,

907
00:39:51,679 --> 00:39:52,559
Murat's Dad

908
00:39:53,039 --> 00:39:54,400
and Ankar's issues

909
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:56,159
could finally be resolved.

910
00:40:02,119 --> 00:40:03,400
What about your own issues?

911
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:21,840
This plan is solid overall,

912
00:40:22,119 --> 00:40:23,320
but it lacks tension.

913
00:40:23,519 --> 00:40:24,960
It can't grab people instantly.

914
00:40:25,480 --> 00:40:27,480
How about we discuss the last project?

915
00:40:27,559 --> 00:40:29,000
That story was quite gripping.

916
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:30,239
The previous plan

917
00:40:30,239 --> 00:40:32,360
was about rescuing a single animal.

918
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,159
It couldn't show

919
00:40:33,159 --> 00:40:35,119
the diversity of Xinjiang's wildlife.

920
00:40:40,239 --> 00:40:41,239
Let's brainstorm more.

921
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:46,440
Bro,

922
00:40:48,519 --> 00:40:49,920
let me introduce everyone.

923
00:40:50,039 --> 00:40:52,280
This is Mingliang, a young artist.

924
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:53,360
I invited him as outside help.

925
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:54,960
He also rescued Xiaoxiao.

926
00:40:57,239 --> 00:40:57,639
Hello.

927
00:40:57,920 --> 00:40:58,840
Xu Lai from PR.

928
00:40:59,320 --> 00:40:59,840
Hello.

929
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:02,440
Come, have a seat.

930
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:02,920
Okay.

931
00:41:04,239 --> 00:41:06,639
Yueyue sent me the requirements

932
00:41:06,639 --> 00:41:07,480
and the previous plan.

933
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:08,960
I have a rough idea.

934
00:41:09,239 --> 00:41:10,400
I'm not great with words,

935
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:11,559
so I drew it out.

936
00:41:11,599 --> 00:41:12,639
You can all take a look.

937
00:41:23,039 --> 00:41:23,480
Honestly,

938
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:25,320
this idea is pretty creative.

939
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:27,159
Using cartoon illustrations

940
00:41:27,159 --> 00:41:28,400
to show the animals

941
00:41:28,599 --> 00:41:29,719
really lowers

942
00:41:29,719 --> 00:41:31,559
our filming costs and difficulty.

943
00:41:32,039 --> 00:41:32,559
Right?

944
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:35,679
Sorry.

945
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:36,800
The idea is great.

946
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:37,480
It really is.

947
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:39,039
I'm just thinking—

948
00:41:39,719 --> 00:41:42,880
maybe the realism might suffer a bit.

949
00:41:43,519 --> 00:41:45,960
How can we organically connect real animals

950
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:47,880
with these cartoon characters?

951
00:41:48,159 --> 00:41:49,360
How do we bridge that gap?

952
00:41:50,119 --> 00:41:51,199
What if we film

953
00:41:51,199 --> 00:41:52,920
a video of an artist sketching?

954
00:41:53,239 --> 00:41:55,519
Use the artist's canvas as the link?

955
00:41:55,960 --> 00:41:56,800
Some video channels

956
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:59,079
show artists filming themselves painting.

957
00:41:59,320 --> 00:42:00,440
We could try that.

958
00:42:02,719 --> 00:42:03,280
I have some here.

959
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:04,039
You can take a look.

960
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,760
Can you do this kind of work?

961
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:24,679
I can give it a try.

962
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:27,480
Don't just "try,"

963
00:42:27,559 --> 00:42:29,119
If he says "try," it means he can do it.

964
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:31,079
Let's go scout locations in the park.

965
00:42:59,239 --> 00:43:00,000
Przewalski's horse.

966
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:02,599
Their most unique feature is the shoulder stripe.

967
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:03,920
It starts at the mane

968
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:05,480
and runs all the way to the tail tip.

969
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:07,199
And their "spring legs."

970
00:43:07,639 --> 00:43:08,320
Crouch lower.

971
00:43:08,360 --> 00:43:09,400
Try shooting from below.

972
00:43:10,079 --> 00:43:10,480
Okay.

973
00:43:23,239 --> 00:43:23,920
I'll help you.
